<Base
  title="Affiliate disclosure | Resting Places"
  description="How Resting Places is funded, which links are affiliate links, and the rules those placements follow."
>
  <h1>Affiliate disclosure</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    Resting Places is free to read. To cover its costs, some pages may contain affiliate links to genealogy research
    services such as Ancestry or MyHeritage. If you subscribe through one of those links, we may earn a commission.
    You pay nothing extra.
  </p>

  <h2>The rules our placements follow</h2>
  <ul class="plain">
    <li>Affiliate links appear only where genuine research intent exists, such as next to interment records, and are always labeled.</li>
    <li>Affiliate links carry <code>rel="sponsored"</code> markup so search engines can identify them.</li>
    <li>No cemetery, person, or fact is included, ranked, or described differently because of an affiliate relationship. The data comes from open records and the rankings are documented counts.</li>
    <li>We do not accept payment for placement in guides or directories.</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    This disclosure follows the US Federal Trade Commission's endorsement guides (16 CFR Part 255).
    Questions: causevic.miz@gmail.com.
  </p>
</Base>
